The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Shimla, Dec. 14: A Chinese national was arrested in Dharamsala on Friday as he did not have a passport or a visa.           
	Lei-xun was arrested from Mcleodganj and did not have a passport or a visa, said Atul Fulzele, the Kangra superintendent of police. The Dalai Lamas official residence is in Mcleodganj. Sources said Lei-xun could be a spy as there have been several instances when Chinese agents have been caught in Dharamsala.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A court has directed the Delhi Municipal Corporation to refund a couple Rs 2.84 lakh, the excess of property tax collected from them. Additional district judge Kamini Lau said the MCD had mentioned the amount as excess in its register, which its officer tried to deny in court.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has held that only a lower court in whose jurisdiction an offence of cheque bounce is committed will try the case. The court said complainants, including financial institutions and banks, should ensure that no inconvenience is caused to the accused.                   
	 Pune (PTI): Suresh Alurkar, the 59-year-old owner of a music shop, was found dead in his flat on Sunday with his throat slit and hands and legs tied, police said. The motive for the murder is yet to be ascertained.                  
	 Panaji (PTI): A Nepali was detained by Goa police on Sunday after he was found suspiciously moving around Dabolim airport in Vasco. The man, who claimed to be Suking Harsh Brajacharya and a native of Kathmandu, was released but arrested again after an unattended Pakistani certificate was found with a photograph matching his face.                   
	 Ludhiana (PTI): Students of a Ludhiana school have claimed a place in the Guiness World Records by preparing a 4,100kg sandwich. The schools principal said the sandwich was made by 160 students of Class VI. Guiness, however, has not given any official confirmation of the record.                                                                                                                         
